Every human enterprise is undeniably better served if there are a few simple and fair rules which all agree to follow. This discussion site is no different.<br>
 <br>
A few rules are needed to assure everyone an equal, fair, and unequivocal voice, free from intimidation, derision, and malice. <br><br>
We are all here to learn, to understand, and to express our feelings and thoughts. This is best done in a way that is respectful to everyone. We can then choose to agree, or agree to disagree, learn, or choose to just walk away, and remain the credit to ourselves I know we all desire.    <br><br>
What, in your mind, are the few simple and fair rules which we all should follow?
